title: NLDS Game 2: Mets vs. Dodgers
text:
The Mets and Dodgers return to Dodger Stadium for Game 2 of the NLDS Saturday night in Los Angeles with a 1-0 series lead. (Credit: Newsday / J. Conrad Williams Jr.) 
Terry Collins speaks to Jeff Wilpons during Game 2 of the NLDS at Dodger Stadium in Los Angeles, Friday, Oct. 10, 2015. (Credit: Newsday / J. Conrad Williams Jr.) 
Mets manager Terry Collins talks to Mets COO Jeff Wilpon before the Mets play the Dodgers in Game 2 of the 2015 NLDS in Los Anageles. (Credit: Newsday / J. Conrad Williams Jr.) 
Mets manager Terry Collins before Game 2 of the 2015 NLDS in Los Angeles.

Mets first baseman Lucas Duda watches on while his team warms up before Game 2 of the 2015 NLDS in Los Angeles. (Credit: Newsday / Thomas A. Ferrara) 
New York Mets David Wright during Batting Practice at Dodgers stadium prior to their National League Division Series game against the Los Angeles Dodgers. Oct. 10, 2015 (Credit: Newsday / Thomas A. Ferrara) 
New York Mets' David Wright during batting practice at Dodger Stadium prior to Game 2 of the National League Division Series against the Los Angeles Dodgers. Oct. 10, 2015. (Credit: Newsday / Thomas A. Ferrara) 
New York Mets fan Evan Cabonell of Texas holds his son Evan Jr. as they watch Mets batting practice at Dodgers stadium before Game 2 of the National League Division Series against the Los Angeles Dodgers. Oct. 10, 2015 (Credit: Newsday / Thomas A. Ferrara) 
New York Mets' David Wright takes swings in the cage during batting practice at Dodger Stadium prior to Game 2 of the National League Division Series against the Los Angeles Dodgers. Oct. 10, 2015
